      • doKeys

        protected void doKeys(Polyad polyad,
                      State state)
        Return a stem of nothing key the keys, so the final stem is of the form 
             {key0=key0,key1=key1,...}
        This is useful in conjunction with the rename keys call, so you can get the keys and do some operations on them then rename the keys in the original stem.
        Parameters:
        polyad -
        state -

        protected void doToList(Polyad polyad,

        Takes a list of arguments (possible stem variables) and creates a new stem from it. The scalars are added with cardinal indexes and stems will have their values added as well in this fashion. (Their keys are not added because you ocould have just added to the existing stem variable).

      • doRenameKeys

        protected void doRenameKeys(Polyad polyad,
                            State state)
        rename_keys(stem., var | list., );

        list. contains entries of the form list.old = new. The result is that each key in the stem. is renamed, but the values are not changed. If a key is in the list at the right and does not correspond to one on the left, it is skipped.
        Parameters:
        polyad -
        state -
